git --version

git config --global user.name  "Name"
git config --global user.email "Email"

to be sure that there is a name and Email write this orders:

git config --global user.name
git config --global user.email


git init 

to remove the all git include the floders and files everything
rm -rf

to remove everything without git storege 
rm -rg .git 


we have to use cd to move to some file and to open the file 
cd~ / path /path / path /path 

to creat a new file 
mkdir (file name)

to move to the file or open it .. 
cd (file name)

git init  to creat a repostery 

git stutus to check the gile situation

ls to see the files in the folder

exit to go out the git bash

touch to add empty file 
forexample

touch name.txt
touch name.html
touch name,py 


to delete a file inside git 
rm file name.txt or py or js ...

to open txt file and change or edit or write in it 
nano name.txt 


after all the changes press ctrl x 
then yes then enter. 
